# HR System — Project Memory

## Identity
- Bilingual (Arabic/English, RTL-aware) HR platform
- Backend: Laravel 13 REST API (PHP 8.4), `api/` directory
- Frontend: Flutter client (web + iOS + Android), `app/` directory
- DB: MySQL/MariaDB in production; SQLite locally

## Architecture
- Auth: Laravel Sanctum tokens + spatie/laravel-permission RBAC
- 6 roles: employee, supervisor, section_manager, hr_director, finance, hr_admin
- Custom `hr.role` middleware (EnsureRole) avoids Sanctum/spatie guard mismatch
- SetLocale middleware reads Accept-Language header (en|ar)
- Approval engine: config-driven chains in `config/hr.php`, generic ApprovalService
- Approvable trait (polymorphic MorphMany to approval_steps) on LeaveRequest, LoanRequest, ShiftChangeRequest, ResignationRequest
- Sensitive fields (basic_salary, national_id) encrypted at rest, hidden by default
- Employee codes: section main_code + employee sub_code = full_code (e.g. "10-0001")
- Attendance: GPS geofenced (haversine), lateness/overtime computed from shift schedule
- Push: FCM via PushNotifier service, device tokens stored per user
- Scheduler: hr:missing-punch-reminders every 5 minutes

## Key Files
- `api/config/hr.php` — domain config (roles, approval chains, leave types, attendance rules)
- `api/app/Services/ApprovalService.php` — multi-step approval engine
- `api/app/Services/AttendanceService.php` — geofence + lateness/overtime
- `api/app/Services/PushNotifier.php` — FCM push notifications
- `api/app/Models/Concerns/Approvable.php` — polymorphic approval trait
- `api/tests/Feature/HrFlowTest.php` — behavioral spec (7 tests)
- `app/lib/core/auth_service.dart` — Flutter auth + biometrics
- `app/lib/core/api_client.dart` — Dio HTTP client with token + locale

## Flutter State
- Provider-based (AuthService, LocaleProvider)
- 5 screens: Dashboard, Attendance, Requests, Approvals (managers), Employees (managers)
- Many API modules not yet in Flutter UI: recruitment, performance, reports, compensation, documents, branch/section CRUD

